{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατεπ-είγω</b>, <br /> <b>press down</b>, χαλεπὸν κατὰ γῆρας ἐπείγει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.623. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>press hard</b>, οἱ χρῆσται κατήπειγον αὐτόν his creditors <b>were pressing</b> him <b>hard</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 33.6, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.61 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κατεπείγει ὕδωρ ῥέον the ebbing water (of the clepsydra) <b>urges</b> him <b>on</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 172e; ἡ φιλοτιμία κατήπειγεν αὐτόν [prev. author] “Ep.” 338e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, οὐδὲν ἡμᾶς ἐστὶ τὸ κατεπεῖγον τὸ μὴ.. σκοπεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 781e; οὐδὲν ὑμᾶς κ. ἀκοῦσαι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.18; τὸ -επεῖγον πράττειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.1.2; τὰ ἀναλώματα τὰ -επείγοντα “PFlor.” 161.5 (3rd c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ κ. alone, the <b>urgent symptom</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 17(2).426; οὔτε τι κωλύει οὔτε -επείγει 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 14; τὰ μάλιστα -επείγοντα 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.132, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.66.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῶν ἐν ἐκείνῳ μὲν τῷ χρόνῳ πραχθέντων, ῥηθῆναι δὲ νῦν οὐ -επειγόντων not <b>urgently requiring</b> mention, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.192; τῆς ὥρας -επειγούσης 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.99.9; θόρυβος φόβος μετὰ φωνῆς -επείγων “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 3.98 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be pressed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator (?) “Oxy.” 1607.43, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.138 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus; περί τινος “PCair.Zen.” 530 (3rd c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>hasten, make haste</b>, ἕπου κατεπείγων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 293: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, Βοιωτοὶ οὐδέν τι κατήπειγον ξυνάψαι <b>were in</b> no <b>haste</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 4.2.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδέν κω κατεπείγων αὐτὸς ἥκειν probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.126. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>hasten</b>, ἐκ Κορίνθου Ἀθήναζε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.51. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>to be anxious, long for</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.37.10, 30.5.9 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: also with <i>dative</i>, <b>press for</b>, τῷ ἐφοδίῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PSI” 6.603.22 (3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7964","accentedUnicode":"κατεπείγω","shortDef":"to coerce","mediumDef":"to coerce","stepGloss":"to coerce","stepTransliteration":"katepeigō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}